ze=1> Disclaimer: This is not a post in favor of nerfing manaburn.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I freely admit that a few melees and clerics with equivilant amounts of AA can farm epic mobs, but my point is they DON'T.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
6 MB wizards vs a well balanced raid group (let's say Warrior, Cleric, Shaman, Bard, Rogue, Monk, or switch out the shaman for another melee if you know you won't slow the mob anyway):<br>
<br>
Where are the truly powerful alt skills in those classes for 27 points? Divine ressurection? A 100% ressurection (requires 3 levels of healing crits woo hoo) with a three day reset time? Mass group buff? Only useful when you have masses to buff (single group doesn't apply). The melee crit ability is nice eye candy for sure, but not something that will increase damage output enough for a single group encounter vs most kunark dragons.<br>
<br>
Most of the melee in the group would try to max out the archetype skills before going after class skills (in general).<br>
<br>
Assuming transportation is no problem, any numer of wizards with manaburn can out kill an equal number of non wizards with an equal number of alt points and all are similarly equipped.<br>
<br>
Sev? Talendor? Gore? 6 MB wizards = dead dragon, our well balanced group, more than likely = dead group (if you can kill any of these dragons with a single group I would love to hear your strategy).<br>
<br>
Now, I have done Faydedar with 4 people (he is not that hard, he doesn't stun or aggro group heals that much). I am sure Ragefire can be done with a single group (though usually the opportunity does not arise because whoever on RN has the camp is too paranoid to try, and rightly so). Any dragon with 32k hp that doesn't stun or CH I am pretty sure a single well-equipped group of melee/cleric/bard could take down. The problem comes when you get to CH/gate and most importantly, stuns. <br>
<br>
With CH/gate a single group just does not have the damage output to prevent casting. With stun, melees get stunned and lose aggro, heals from the cleric (in my experience) gain lots of aggro and the cleric will die if they cannot get a DA/DB off, or the cleric cannot heal at all (using CH is a mistake because in 10 seconds there are plenty of opportunities to get stunned, using faster heals basically would let the tank die slowly because he is taking more damage than healing will make up for). And while the MT slowly dies from getting fewer HP healed than he takes damage for, everyone else in the group is already dead because they aren't getting healed at all. Group heals = instant attention from said stunning mob = dead cleric. Keep in mind this is a made up single group encounter vs Talendor/Sev (both stun).<br>
<br>
My point is, if you think an equivalent group of melee/cleric vs a MB group can kill the same things, you need to research a bit more. Again, if you can poke holes in my argument, please do. I would love to take out Gore/Sev/Talendor with a single group of melee/cleric. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufynalwiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fynalwiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 828<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/15/02 9:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How MB will be Nerfed(tm), taking bets...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Regardless of you're feelings on whether it needs to be Nerfed, I think we all know it will be. Here's my bet on how it will happen, after seeing all the Nerfs since beta3 <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
