<br>
The name is usrbinperl dashw, which is derived from the unix command:<br>
<br>
/usr/bin/perl -w<br>
<br>
/usr/bin is usually the directory where the perl application resides, and -w is a parameter of some sort, but it's been awhile and I couldn't tell you what it is.<br>
<br>
Perl is a scripting language used by unix clones and is a very powerful, but high level programming language.  It's great for writing EQ parsers <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Note that usrbinperl dashw got changed to Xasha Maelstrom. <p><center>
