1. Wizard uses manaburn, magician doesnt provide rods.<br>
<br>
2. Wizard uses manaburn, magician provides rods.<br>
<br>
3. Wizard doesnt use manaburn, magician provides rods if wizard runs out of mana.<br>
<br>
The article shows that case 2 is better then case 1. But that doesnt prove that case 2 is better then case 3. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A> at: 9/1/02 6:00:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 5816<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/2/02 9:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Er, no</span><hr size=1> Well, the theory is, Wizards run up and Manaburn then get mod rods and refuel their mana to full and nuke.  So you kind of get both, but Mages STILL do a ton of damage with nukes and pets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utorcerarcana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torcer Arcana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 2013<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/2/02 4:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How MB will be Nerfed(tm), taking bets...</span><hr size=1> If it is &quot;nerfed,&quot; then it will be indirect, by increasing the HPs of old world and Kunark MoBs. <p>60 Sorcerer | The BoD | The Nameless

